----------------------------------------------------------------------
SCOPE OF LICENSE
----------------------------------------------------------------------

The Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0) license
applies ONLY to the following components of the Zaan Koshur project:

• Documentation
• Metadata schemas and standards
• Transcription rules and guidelines
• Scripts, source code, and utilities
• Non-audio textual resources

Voice recordings, raw audio files, processed audio, and any derived
acoustic or biometric representations are NOT publicly licensed under
CC BY 4.0.

Access to voice data is restricted and controlled exclusively by the
project owner and authorized maintainers. Audio data may not be shared,
redistributed, published, or reused without explicit written permission
from the project owner.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
ZAAN KOSHUR — ADDITIONAL ETHICAL USE CLAUSE
----------------------------------------------------------------------

Because this project involves language material and voice contributions
from real Kashmiri speakers, the following ethical requirements apply:

1. Voice recordings must never be used for surveillance, biometric
   identification, speaker profiling, or any activity that violates
   personal privacy.

2. Project resources must not be used to create harmful, abusive,
   exploitative, or culturally disrespectful applications.

3. Contributors’ voices must remain anonymous.
   No attempt may be made to identify, trace, or deanonymize speakers.

4. Models trained using Zaan Koshur resources must not be used for
   political manipulation, harassment, discrimination, or
   misinformation.

5. Any derivative work must preserve the spirit of cultural respect,
   linguistic preservation, and community benefit that this project
   represents.

6. If contributors request removal of their data, reasonable efforts
   must be made by authorized holders to delete the data and any derived
   artifacts where feasible.

Use of any Zaan Koshur project resources signifies agreement with the
applicable license terms and the ethical requirements defined herein.

